# jsm-import-ready patch artifact
#
# flywheel-ovp71: remove executable bit from skill scripts to satisfy JSM
# EXECUTABLE_NOT_ALLOWED policy. Skills are currently UNMANAGED by JSM
# (not in ~/.claude/skills/.jsm-manifest.json or .jsm-installed.txt).
# Direct mutation applied per dispatch contract for unmanaged skills.
# This artifact documents the change so JSM can later import the skills
# without re-introducing the executable-bit conflict.
#
# Skills affected:
#   - /Users/josh/.claude/skills/nango-integrations/scripts/*.sh (18 files)
#   - /Users/josh/.claude/skills/railway-api/scripts/*.sh (1 file)
#
# Apply to a fresh JSM-managed copy via:
#
#   chmod -x scripts/*.sh
#
# Or, when applying to a directory that came from a JSM source repo:
#
#   find <skill-path>/scripts -type f -name '*.sh' -exec chmod -x {} \;
#
# Behavior preservation: shell scripts retain their `#!/usr/bin/env bash`
# (or equivalent) shebang lines. Consumers must invoke them via `bash <path>`
# rather than `<path>` directly. This is the canonical JSM-policy-compliant
# invocation pattern.
#
